    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-03T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2602: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-03T23:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 3, 1920, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received January 3, 8.46 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Your 9441, December 27. I learn at the Foreign Office that the French
                    Government’s contention that the disbandment of troops should be a <hi
                        rend="italic">sine qua non</hi> to the issuance of the loan has been
                    withdrawn and that it so informed the British Embassy here on December 30th. The
                    French Government, however, will insist that unnecessary troops be disbanded at
                    the earliest possible moment not only by the Northern but also by the Southern
                    factions and proportionally. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
